This paper deals with privacy in protocols for set problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) to measure privacy, and discusses algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for solving the set problems. Additionally, the paper mentions fairness in the protocols, which could fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) or machine learning (cs.LG).
